ِﮭﺎﻠْ َھأ ﻋﻠﻰ
 َﺮاﻗﺑ ْ َﺖﻨَﺟ ﮭﺎ ِﺴْ َﻔﻧ / 
 ِﺶ
To have only one’s self to blame; to dig one’s own grave; to bring something 
bad on oneself; to ask for trouble; to be one’s own fault; it serves one right. 
